INSTALL — import_pentacam
=========================

Prerequisites
-------------

- Rust toolchain (install via https://rustup.rs)
- Linux x86_64 (Ubuntu 22.04+ or equivalent, glibc >= 2.35)
- Internet connection (for downloading ONNX Runtime)
- Optional: NVIDIA GPU with CUDA drivers for GPU acceleration

Quick Start
-----------

    ./configure
    make install

This will:
1. Download ONNX Runtime (GPU version if CUDA is detected, CPU otherwise)
2. Build the release binary
3. Install to ~/.local/lib/import_pentacam/ with a wrapper in ~/.local/bin/

After installation, run:

    import_pentacam --help

Configure Options
-----------------

    ./configure                    Auto-detect everything
    ./configure --cpu-only         Force CPU-only build (no CUDA, smaller download)
    ./configure --ort-dir DIR      Use an existing ONNX Runtime installation
    ./configure --prefix DIR       Install to DIR instead of ~/.local

Make Targets
------------

    make                Build release binary only
    make dist           Build + assemble dist/import_pentacam/ with all
                        libraries and models (portable, self-contained)
    make dist-tar       Build + create .tar.gz archive for distribution
    make install        Build + install to PREFIX (default: ~/.local)
    make clean          Remove build artifacts

Distributing
------------

After `make dist`, the dist/import_pentacam/ folder is fully self-contained.
Copy it to any Linux x86_64 machine and run directly — no installation or
environment variables needed:

    cd import_pentacam/
    ./import_pentacam --help

For GPU support, the target machine needs NVIDIA CUDA drivers installed
(the CUDA runtime libraries are bundled).

System-wide Installation (as root)
----------------------------------

    ./configure --prefix /usr/local
    sudo make install

This installs to /usr/local/lib/import_pentacam/ with a wrapper script
in /usr/local/bin/.

Notes
-----

- ONNX Runtime is downloaded to ort/ in the source directory. To avoid
  re-downloading, keep this directory across clean builds.
- The binary uses RUNPATH=$ORIGIN to find its shared libraries relative
  to itself. No LD_LIBRARY_PATH configuration is needed.
- OCR models (~100 MB) are bundled in the models/ subdirectory and must
  be in the same relative location as the binary.
- GPU memory: expect ~8-34 GB VRAM usage during OCR. The software falls
  back to CPU if GPU is unavailable or runs out of memory.
